SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 411
By Crowe
A RESOLUTION to honor Dr. William Turney Williams, Chairman
of the Washington County Republican Party.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable public servants who work to improve the quality of life for their fellow
citizens through their involvement in the political process; and
WHEREAS, Dr. William Turney Williams has proven himself to be an invaluable asset to
the Washington County Republican Party, which he has ably and devotedly served as
chairman; and
WHEREAS, a native of Albuquerque, New Mexico, Mr. Williams grew up as one of six
children in a military family; his father, a Colonel in the Air Force, served as Commander of the
Office of Aerospace Research in Belgium; and
WHEREAS, while attending high school in Belgium, Turney Williams earned a place on
the European All-Star tennis team; he earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Chemistry from
Northern State College in Aberdeen, South Dakota, and his Master of Science degree in Bio-
Chemistry from the University of Nebraska in Lincoln; and
WHEREAS, choosing to devote his life to medicine, he earned his Bachelor of Science
degree in Medicine from the University of South Dakota School of Medicine and his Doctor of
Medicine degree at the prestigious Washington University School of Medicine in St. Louis,
Missouri, graduating in 1979; and
WHEREAS, in 1988, Dr. Williams moved to Johnson City to begin his medical career at
Johnson City Medical Center; he later joined Anesthesia Associates before founding Pain
Medicine Associates, spending decades helping community members manage chronic pain and
