improve their quality of life; he only recently retired from practicing medicine, after a
distinguished thirty-seven-year career as a physician in East Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, beyond his professional accomplishments, Dr. Turney Williams has been a
pillar of civic engagement, serving as Chairman of the Washington County Republican Party for
a number of years and remaining active in local politics; and
WHEREAS, his commitment to service extends to animal welfare through his volunteer
work with and donations to the Appalachian Highlands Humane Society and Washington
County Animal Shelter; and
WHEREAS, passionate about the outdoors, Dr. Williams is an accomplished
mountaineer, having conquered Mt. Rainier twice, summited Mt. Whitney, and tackled
numerous "fourteeners" in Colorado; and
WHEREAS, his love for nature manifests in various activities, including fishing, skiing,
hiking, backpacking, camping, mountain biking, and kayaking; when not exploring the
wilderness or taking care of animals, Dr. Turney Williams can usually be found immersed in a
history book; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Williams is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service and
political engagement that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and he
should be specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Washington County
Republican Party Chairman Dr. William Turney Williams, salute his unswerving commitment to
living the examined life with courage and conviction, and extend to him our best wishes for
much continued success and happiness.
